{{Otheruses|復活 (消歧義)}} 
[[File:Jerg_Ratgeb_001.jpg|thumb]]]]
'''復活'''（英語：Resurrection 或 anastasis）是[[死亡|死亡]]後[[生命|生命]]回復的[[概念|概念]]。在許多[[信仰|信仰]]中存在死而復生的[[神祇|神祇]]或[[神聖|神聖]]人物，如[[歐西里斯|歐西里斯]]、[[阿多尼斯|阿多尼斯]]、[[耶穌|耶穌]]、[[哪吒|哪吒]]等。[[轉世|轉世]]是其他宗教[[假設|假設]]的類似過程，它涉及同一個人或神靈回到不同的身體，而不是同一個身體。

死人的復活是[[亞伯拉罕宗教|亞伯拉罕宗教]]的標準[[末世論|末世論]]。作為一個宗教概念，它被用於兩個不同的方面：對當前和正在進行的個體[[靈魂|靈魂]]復活的信仰（基督教理想主義、[[已實現終末論|已實現終末論]]），或者對死者在[[時間終結|末世]]的單一復活的信仰世界。有些人認為靈魂是人們復活的實際載體。<ref>{{cite web|title=Gregory of Nyssa: "On the Soul and the Resurrection:" However far from each other their natural propensity and their inherent forces of repulsion urge them, and debar each from mingling with its opposite, none the less will the soul be near each by its power of recognition, and will persistently cling to the familiar atoms, until their concourse after this division again takes place in the same way, for that fresh formation of the dissolved body which will properly be, and be called, resurrection|url=http://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/npnf205.x.iii.ii.html|publisher=Ccel.org|access-date=2021-12-22|archive-date=2012-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121002015536/http://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/npnf205.x.iii.ii.html}}</ref>

[[耶穌被釘十字架|耶穌的死]]和[[耶穌復活|復活]]是基督教的中心焦點。[[基督教神學|基督教神學]]爭論隨之而來的是關於什麼樣的復活是真實的—是靈體進入天堂的[[靈性|靈性]]復活，或是[[人體|人體]]生命恢復的物質復活。<ref>As in the [[Apostles'_Creed|Apostles' Creed]]: "I believe in the Holy Spirit, the holy catholic Church, the communion of saints, the forgiveness of sins, the resurrection of the body, and life everlasting." [http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/12792a.htm Catholic Encyclopedia: General Resurrection] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/12792a.htm |date=20220612233611 }}: "Resurrection is the rising again from the dead, the resumption of life. The [[Fourth_Lateran_Council|Fourth Lateran Council]] (1215) teaches that all men, whether [[Chosen_people#Christianity|elect]] or [[reprobate|reprobate]], "will rise again with their own bodies which they now bear about with them" (chapter "''Firmiter''"). In the language of the [[Creed|creeds]] and professions of faith this return to life is called resurrection of the body (''resurrectio carnis, resurrectio mortuoram, anastasis ton nekron'') for a double reason: first, since the [[Immortality_of_the_soul|soul cannot die]], it cannot be said to return to life; second the [[heretical|heretical]] contention of [[Hymenaeus_(Ephesian)|Hymeneus and Philitus]] that the [[Scriptures|Scriptures]] denote by resurrection not the return to life of the body, but the rising of the soul from the death of [[Christian_views_on_sin|sin]] to the life of [[Grace_(Christianity)|grace]], must be excluded."</ref> 雖然大多數基督徒相信耶穌從死裡復活和升天是在一個物質身體裡，但有些人相信它是靈性上的。<ref>{{cite web|title=According to Paul of Tarsus, the resurrection transformed Jesus into the Christ, the Son of God and Savior of the world. Christ's resurrected body was not a resuscitated physical body, but a new body of a spiritual/celestial nature: the natural body comes first and then the spiritual body (1 Cor. 15:46). Paul never says that the earthly body becomes immortal.|url=http://www.religioustolerance.org/symes01.htm|last=Symes|first=R. C.|publisher=religioustolerance.org|access-date=2021-12-22|archive-date=2012-12-09|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CmVetRQ4?url=http://www.religioustolerance.org/symes01.htm}}</ref><ref>The Watchtower Society claims that Jesus was not raised in His actual physical human body, but rather was raised as an invisible spirit being—what He was before, the archangel Michael. They believe that Christ's post-Resurrection appearances on earth were on-the-spot manifestations and materializations of flesh and bones, with different forms, that the Apostles did not immediately recognize. Their explanation for the statement "a spirit hath not flesh and bones" is that Christ was saying that he was not a ghostly apparition, but a true materialization in flesh, to be seen and touched, as proof that he was actually raised. But that, in fact, the risen Christ was, in actuality, a divine spirit being, who made himself visible and invisible at will. The Christian Congregation of Jehovah’s Witnesses believes that Christ’s perfect manhood was forever sacrificed at Calvary, and that it was not actually taken back. They state: "...in his resurrection he ‘became a life-giving spirit.’ That was why for most of the time he was invisible to his faithful apostles... He needs no human body any longer... The human body of flesh, which Jesus Christ laid down forever as a ransom sacrifice, was disposed of by God’s power."—Things in Which it is Impossible for God to Lie, pages 332, 354.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Resurrection Theories|url=http://www.gospel-mysteries.net/resurrection-theories.html|access-date=2013-05-04|publisher=Gospel-mysteries.net|archive-date=2012-12-09|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CmVffbOv?url=http://www.gospel-mysteries.net/resurrection-theories.html}}</ref>

該概念的闡釋不一定與不死靈魂的宗教[[信念|信念]]相關。

== 宗教及哲學上的復活 ==
=== 古埃及人 ===
復活的思想，存在於古今的[[宗教|宗教]]中。古代[[埃及|埃及]]人相信，人死後可以復活，但要保存[[屍體|屍體]]。因此不少古埃及人選擇將自己[[遺體|遺體]]製成[[木乃伊|木乃伊]]，有些還建造[[金字塔|金字塔]]，以便保存遺體，等候復活或復活的可能。

=== 基督教、天主教及猶太教 ===
古代[[猶太教|猶太教]]信仰，相信肉身復活。根據《[[新约聖經|新约聖經]]》記載，[[耶穌基督|耶穌基督]]在被釘死後三天復活。相信耶穌死後復活乃[[基督教|基督教]]的重要教義信仰的根基:
: 假如死人復活是沒有的事，基督也就沒有復活，假如基督沒有復活，那麼，我們的宣講便是空的，你們的[[信仰|信仰]]也是空的。（哥林多前書：15，13-14）

現今[[天主教|天主教]]、[[東正教|東正教]]和[[基督新教|基督新教]]相信，人死後[[靈魂|靈魂]]和[[身體|身體]]都會復活到[[天堂|天堂]]或[[地獄|地獄]]。各[[基督教派|基督教派]]對復活闡述的細節卻略有不同。在宗教史上，[[古希臘哲學|古希臘哲學]]曾對猶太教對基督宗教所信仰的復活產生影響。<ref>《論靈魂和身體復活》，德爾圖良，道風書社，2001年5月版 </ref>

在某些場合下復活和[[輪迴|輪迴]]相似，即沒有涉及復活的對象是否保持同一個身體或靈魂的連續性，如[[啟示錄|啟示錄]]的未來世界。

==疑似死後復活==
{{參見|瀕死經驗}}
現時有不少疑似死後復活的例子。一般是因為[[病人|病者]]進入[[深度昏迷|深度昏迷]] (俗稱假死) 而被誤判為死亡，但在[[葬禮|送葬]]時突然甦醒，像『死後復活』一樣。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sohu.com/20050622/n226035998.shtml|title=死亡少年殡仪馆内突然复活|publisher=搜孤新聞|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526122931/http://news.sohu.com/20050622/n226035998.shtml|archive-date=2020-05-26|dead-url=no|accessdate=2020-05-26}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zhong-yao.net/cs/xl/jb/200804/128827.html|title=少女在被火化前复活家人误以为其病亡|publisher=中醫中藥網|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120926224155/http://www.zhong-yao.net/cs/xl/jb/200804/128827.html|archive-date=2012-09-26|dead-url=yes|accessdate=2020-05-26}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/society/2007-06/08/content_6213426.htm|title=重慶少女在被火化前復活家人誤以為其病亡|publisher=新華網|archive-url=
https://web.archive.org/web/20090105181114/http://news.xinhuanet.com/society/2007-06/08/content_6213426.htm|archive-date=2009-01-05|dead-url=yes|
accessdate=2020-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.pchome.com.tw/society/tvbs/20110525/index-13062973267155039002.html|title=嚇壞法醫！癌末男輕生　死8小時復活|publisher=TVBS|archive-url=
https://web.archive.org/web/20110528120216/http://news.pchome.com.tw/society/tvbs/20110525/index-13062973267155039002.html|archive-date=2011-05-28|dead-url=yes|
accessdate=2011-05-25}}
</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://scitech.people.com.cn/BIG5/6806632.html|title=智利一名八旬老翁棺材中突然"復活"|publisher=人民網|archive-url=
https://web.archive.org/web/20190609203922/http://scitech.people.com.cn/BIG5/6806632.html|archive-date=2019-06-09|dead-url=yes|
accessdate=2019-06-09}}</ref>在有些情况下，病人会感觉自己像是去了[[天堂|天堂]]或[[地狱|地狱]]一样，詳見[[瀕死經驗|瀕死經驗]]。

== 科幻及未來學上復活的可能性 ==
除了從[[宗教|宗教]]的角度以外，亦有人認為[[醫療|醫療]]及[[生物科技|生物科技]]最終能使[[人類|人類]]和其他[[生物|生物]]復活。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scitech.people.com.cn/BIG5/25893/3724349.html|title=人死復生不再是夢 動物實驗已成功|publisher=人民網|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526122954/http://scitech.people.com.cn/BIG5/25893/3724349.html|archive-date=2020-05-26|dead-url=yes|accessdate=2005-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news3.xinhuanet.com/st/2003-07/30/content_1000590.htm|title=人俄罗斯科学家称人体温降低两度可多活120到150年|publisher=人民網|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809101951/http://news3.xinhuanet.com/st/2003-07/30/content_1000590.htm|archive-date=2011-08-09|dead-url=yes|accessdate=2010-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tech.sina.com.cn/d/2005-09-23/0718727260.shtml|title=死而复生动物实验获成功 专家观点激烈碰撞|publisher=新浪網科技時代|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526123006/http://tech.sina.com.cn/d/2005-09-23/0718727260.shtml|archive-date=2020-05-26|dead-url=no|accessdate=2020-01-01}}</ref>

有少數的現代人，選擇以[[人體冷凍技術|人體冷凍技術]]或[[化學腦保存|化學腦保存]]等[[遺體保存技術|遺體保存技術]]的形式來保存自己的[[遺體|遺體]]和[[大腦|大腦]]，幻想並等候未來可能出現的先進科技和醫學能使他們復活。 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enet.com.cn/article/2006/0814/A20060814162176.shtml|title=复活冷冻人体不再是梦|publisher=eNet 中國IT信息與商務門戶|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927203220/http://www.enet.com.cn/article/2006/0814/A20060814162176.shtml|archive-date=2007-09-27|dead-url=yes|accessdate=2007-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.100md.com/html/Dir/2004/03/28/68/445.htm|title=千年古尸能复活吗？|publisher=百拇醫葯|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060109023637/http://www.100md.com/html/Dir/2004/03/28/68/445.htm|archive-date=2006-01-09|dead-url=no|accessdate=2020-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ido.3mt.com.cn/Article/200605/show356985c32p1.html|title=齐齐哈尔木乃伊死因之谜|publisher=ido社区|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100404090043/http://ido.3mt.com.cn/Article/200605/show356985c32p1.html|archive-date=2010-04-04|dead-url=yes|accessdate=2010-04-04}}</ref>

